    <text id="R14610652T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Union General Alfred Torbert writes to General Morgan in May, 1865, to report
                    that Union cavalry are now stationed in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    HDQRS. ARMY OF THE SHENANDOAH,
                    <name type="recipient">Brevet Brig.-Gen. MORGAN,<lb/> Chief of Staff, Middle
                        Military Division, Washington, D. C.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-05-01">May 1, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Dispatch from Gen. Hancock received. Col. Reed with 600 cavalry is now in
                    Staunton with seven days' supplies. Does the general wish the expedition to go
                    up there before Col. R.'s return?</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>A. T. A. TORBERT,<lb/> Brevet Maj.-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
